qas.question: What happened to China after the 20th century revolutions?

answers.text: shifting alliances of China's regional warlords waged war for control of the Beijing government.

qas.question: Who ultimately gained control of the Beijing government?
Why was there not a new era of governance in Beijing?

answers.text: because other warlords did not acknowledge the transitory governments in this period and were a law unto themselves.
